<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><dmn:definitions xmlns:dmn="https://www.omg.org/spec/DMN/20240513/MODEL/" xmlns="https://kiegroup.org/dmn/_0DCC505E-71B4-4C29-8848-4006623FE51A" xmlns:feel="https://www.omg.org/spec/DMN/20240513/FEEL/" xmlns:kie="https://kie.org/dmn/extensions/1.0" xmlns:dmndi="https://www.omg.org/spec/DMN/20230324/DMNDI/" xmlns:di="http://www.omg.org/spec/DMN/20180521/DI/" xmlns:dc="http://www.omg.org/spec/DMN/20180521/DC/" id="_14645A68-5630-4A6F-899F-4FF825252CCD" name="New Hiring Offer" typeLanguage="https://www.omg.org/spec/DMN/20240513/FEEL/" namespace="https://kiegroup.org/dmn/_0DCC505E-71B4-4C29-8848-4006623FE51A"><dmn:description>## Overview
Use this model to generate a job offer (category and salary) for a software engineering candidate based on their years of experience and number of skills. It maps experience tiers to job categories and computes a base salary plus a skill-count bonus.
## Inputs
- CandidateData (object) — candidate profile with fields: name (string), lastName (string), email (string), experience (number, years of professional experience), skills (list of strings, e.g. ["Java","AWS"])
## Use cases
- Automated offer generation during recruiting pipeline
- Salary benchmarking for new hires
- Category classification for engineering candidates
## Do not use when
- Evaluating existing employees for promotions (experience thresholds may not apply)
- Roles outside software engineering (categories are fixed to SE/SSE/Architect)
- Compensation models that include equity, bonuses, or benefits beyond base salary
## Main entry points
- Offer (tOffer) — returns category (string enum) and salary (number)</dmn:description>
  <dmn:extensionElements/>
  <dmn:itemDefinition id="_91B22404-81DF-44E7-9084-6416BF211BCC" name="tCandidateData" isCollection="false">
    <dmn:itemComponent id="_657BB44B-D8B2-490A-B383-F63EF31E781E" name="name" isCollection="false">
      <dmn:typeRef>string</dmn:typeRef>
    </dmn:itemComponent>
    <dmn:itemComponent id="_F004E7F6-6993-4CA2-8029-C3A87C8A15A8" name="lastName" isCollection="false">
      <dmn:typeRef>string</dmn:typeRef>
    </dmn:itemComponent>
    <dmn:itemComponent id="_E9314196-BF96-4014-9548-2BB15D125B34" name="email" isCollection="false">
      <dmn:typeRef>string</dmn:typeRef>
    </dmn:itemComponent>
    <dmn:itemComponent id="_D554122C-2BF1-4F1C-AAF2-DC7EBB72E817" name="experience" isCollection="false">
      <dmn:typeRef>number</dmn:typeRef>
    </dmn:itemComponent>
    <dmn:itemComponent id="_03ACF59E-4EC6-4C79-AE55-427BD51429BD" name="skills" isCollection="true">
      <dmn:typeRef>string</dmn:typeRef>
    </dmn:itemComponent>
  </dmn:itemDefinition>
  <dmn:itemDefinition id="_76F919CD-3E75-4EE2-AD60-FB0627E0DA54" name="tOffer" isCollection="false">
    <dmn:itemComponent id="_C4ABF342-EEB6-4CA6-AAC1-7C6D50A1DD02" name="salary" isCollection="false">
      <dmn:typeRef>number</dmn:typeRef>
    </dmn:itemComponent>
    <dmn:itemComponent id="_3C2A61B7-AD85-4AF3-B904-51038920EF93" name="category" isCollection="false">
      <dmn:typeRef>string</dmn:typeRef>
      <dmn:allowedValues kie:constraintType="enumeration" id="_8C8338A1-7CA6-48D8-AECB-3D5082333316">
        <dmn:text>"Software Engineer", "Senior Software Engineer", "Software Architect"</dmn:text>
      </dmn:allowedValues>
    </dmn:itemComponent>
  </dmn:itemDefinition>
  <dmn:decision id="_26299D78-4931-4077-A636-1364B97AB94F" name="Offer"><dmn:description>## What it decides
Use this decision to compute the job category and base salary for a software engineering candidate.
## Call when
- A new candidate has been evaluated and a formal offer needs to be generated
## Do not call when
- The candidate is being evaluated for an internal transfer or promotion
- The role is outside the Software Engineer / Senior Software Engineer / Software Architect career ladder
## Inputs
- CandidateData.experience (number) — drives category tier: [0..5) → Software Engineer, [5..10) → Senior Software Engineer, &gt;=10 → Software Architect
- CandidateData.skills (list) — skill count multiplied by 150 gives the salary bonus
## Output
- category (string) — one of: "Software Engineer", "Senior Software Engineer", "Software Architect"
- salary (number) — base salary (22000 / 33000 / 44000) plus skill bonus (count(skills) * 150)
## Examples
- experience=3, skills=["Java","Python"] → category="Software Engineer", salary=22300
- experience=7, skills=["Java"] → category="Senior Software Engineer", salary=33150
- experience=12, skills=["Java","AWS","Go"] → category="Software Architect", salary=44450</dmn:description>
    <dmn:extensionElements/>
    <dmn:variable id="_1C79A32D-6535-4209-9840-D4FF6FF52CA9" name="Offer" typeRef="tOffer"/>
    <dmn:informationRequirement id="_87BE8DEF-9B4D-45EC-8E59-6CD9D0613DCF">
      <dmn:requiredInput href="#_59F676A7-D122-4FAB-8ABB-F1E0CC997C08"/>
    </dmn:informationRequirement>
    <dmn:context id="_6CF8329F-A45C-4FC8-AEDD-F2DA34BCD9CC" label="Offer" typeRef="tOffer">
      <dmn:contextEntry id="_15D30C85-0EF7-4052-943E-0B3F14EC9C8E">
        <dmn:variable id="_F97FBBC2-9B78-4280-8053-B5089E422B35" name="SalaryBonus" typeRef="number"/>
        <dmn:literalExpression id="_DE5ECE12-3B62-497F-9A5F-8DFE8D5B440B">
          <dmn:text>count(CandidateData.skills) * 150</dmn:text>
        </dmn:literalExpression>
      </dmn:contextEntry>
      <dmn:contextEntry id="_4F3F8949-B861-41B4-B14A-B275248ED835">
        <dmn:variable id="_CE19A7DC-A559-482A-93A8-38786291B11C" name="Offer" typeRef="tOffer"/>
        <dmn:decisionTable id="_839000A0-8C02-4FD7-A079-9DCA9C2D9C67" hitPolicy="UNIQUE" preferredOrientation="Rule-as-Row">
          <dmn:input id="_2003EFC0-4A87-43FA-80B1-25C14F0AB2FF">
            <dmn:inputExpression id="_663F281B-8A30-44DC-9DA5-B141831D552B" typeRef="number">
              <dmn:text>CandidateData.experience</dmn:text>
            </dmn:inputExpression>
          </dmn:input>
          <dmn:output id="_BCCDA650-A716-4BA4-9B3D-4CD8AE93CB79" name="category" typeRef="string">
            <dmn:outputValues kie:constraintType="enumeration" id="_78F5B0AC-CE91-4BEC-8B26-121FF0C0BC2A">
              <dmn:text>"Software Engineer", "Senior Software Engineer", "Software Architect"</dmn:text>
            </dmn:outputValues>
          </dmn:output>
          <dmn:output id="_FF119A4B-E564-438A-99D9-4D1B26E519F1" name="salary" typeRef="number"/>
          <dmn:annotation name="annotation-1"/>
          <dmn:rule id="_2E67A292-D088-4ED7-AC9D-A7D85C3B6188">
            <dmn:inputEntry id="_5082A566-8E83-4441-B446-A69E5BE4D81E">
              <dmn:text>[0..5)</dmn:text>
            </dmn:inputEntry>
            <dmn:outputEntry id="_BF300CEA-9C67-4A48-9E63-781B94552D6F">
              <dmn:text>"Software Engineer"</dmn:text>
            </dmn:outputEntry>
            <dmn:outputEntry id="_7B4EBA06-D280-436F-80E6-B6631BED7E8F">
              <dmn:text>22000 + SalaryBonus </dmn:text>
            </dmn:outputEntry>
            <dmn:annotationEntry>
              <dmn:text/>
            </dmn:annotationEntry>
          </dmn:rule>
          <dmn:rule id="_1322663C-FAD9-48BA-A893-8076ED7D2D55">
            <dmn:inputEntry id="_6801EF6E-ED61-41DF-9810-7D9118A1F611">
              <dmn:text>[5..10)</dmn:text>
            </dmn:inputEntry>
            <dmn:outputEntry id="_43E9D87D-ECE5-4298-B98A-9E69D93B967B">
              <dmn:text>"Senior Software Engineer"</dmn:text>
            </dmn:outputEntry>
            <dmn:outputEntry id="_CF868CA5-C53A-4ECD-9167-5C55F858FF7F">
              <dmn:text>33000 + SalaryBonus</dmn:text>
            </dmn:outputEntry>
            <dmn:annotationEntry>
              <dmn:text/>
            </dmn:annotationEntry>
          </dmn:rule>
          <dmn:rule id="_1104ED9E-0910-40F9-A0C3-911BF018C545">
            <dmn:inputEntry id="_3D058456-EA96-4D78-9BF1-9AEDF3755C47">
              <dmn:text>&gt;=10</dmn:text>
            </dmn:inputEntry>
            <dmn:outputEntry id="_061D4DC8-069B-43C7-9200-C20D11692D8F">
              <dmn:text>"Software Architect"</dmn:text>
            </dmn:outputEntry>
            <dmn:outputEntry id="_C7269E79-EE4D-440C-99F7-C5F474F15E2F">
              <dmn:text>44000 + SalaryBonus</dmn:text>
            </dmn:outputEntry>
            <dmn:annotationEntry>
              <dmn:text/>
            </dmn:annotationEntry>
          </dmn:rule>
        </dmn:decisionTable>
      </dmn:contextEntry>
      <dmn:contextEntry id="_B88057A5-2BB9-4570-AB66-97204DE5CF06">
        <dmn:literalExpression id="_3676400A-0460-43CC-A96A-B28B460E4D19">
          <dmn:text>Offer</dmn:text>
        </dmn:literalExpression>
      </dmn:contextEntry>
    </dmn:context>
  </dmn:decision>
  <dmn:inputData id="_59F676A7-D122-4FAB-8ABB-F1E0CC997C08" name="CandidateData"><dmn:description>Structured candidate profile required to compute the hiring offer. Fields: name (string), lastName (string), email (string), experience (number — years of professional experience, must be &gt;= 0), skills (array of strings — list of technical skill names, e.g. ["Java","Kubernetes","AWS"]). All fields are expected; experience and skills directly drive the offer calculation.</dmn:description>
    <dmn:extensionElements/>
    <dmn:variable id="_EF5D30F7-00BF-47E2-9655-D1D21B799F5C" name="CandidateData" typeRef="tCandidateData"/>
  </dmn:inputData>
